A surpringly large menu of variations of meat sandwiches.   The location isn't. Easy to reach from my home by bus, but it is close by car.  I had a ride one day and we decided to have a late lunch at Arby's.  3 PM on a weekday afternoon there were almost no other customers there.  No waiting.  I ordered their old standby sandwich: hot roast beef and cheddar cheese.  The meat is marinated and I suspect it is served with a high salt content..  The taste was good but the texture of the meat was a little off for roast beef.  I can see where the rumors that they use fabricated beef come from.  They firmly deny those allegations.  The sandwich came on a large soft onion roll.  Not a wonderfully great roll, but it was good.  They have a wide self serve selection of fountain drinks (free refills)  Unsweetened iced tea was among the choices so I was happy on that front.  Too much salt is a medical no-no for me. That will probably keep me from a return visit to Arby's.  I will make a point of looking up their nutrition facts before I again go there.

That was my first time eating at Arby's. My co-worker and I were super excited and had a hard time selecting a sandwich because the pictures looked so appealing. Finally, we. Chose their famous roast beef classic, a fully loaded fries and a Jamocha shake. We were extremely disappointed by the look of our sandwiches and it tasted like plastic. We then proceed to add some of their sauce in our sandwiches, hoping it would give some flavor... Nope! Yucky!!! Desperate, I added some salt and pepper but the sandwiches could not be saved! Now, we started to eat the fully loaded fries to remove the horrible taste of the sandwich in our mouth... Misery! I was at this point sure thatbthis place was not serving real food. The yellow thing that is suppose to be cheese tasted like nothing. The fries were chewy. Bad experience. Even their Jamocha shake tasted like chocolate milk!!! I was expecting the taste of mocha instead of plain chocolate milk! Arby's it is time to rethink of your taste and the look of your food and please don't give customers false information. Lower your price or just move to another town with clients with lower expectations!!! I give you a 2 stars because the employees are nice and the place clean.

I'm not some big fan of Arby's or in love with their food but I see no reason to deduct any stars if you're familiar with Arby's and know what to expect from their menu. The store is clean, plenty of parking with a drive through, 2 convenient entrances into the parking lot, service is fast, and prices are decent. I'm not thrilled about their roast beef (it's been described as paste-like that solidifies after they bake it) but they have seasoned curly fries and their lamb gyros are not too bad (2 decent size gyros for $6). If you're not familiar with Arby's you're not missing anything but if you are in the mood for Arby's there's no reason not to visit this location.

Like most Arby's, it's easy to order and staff tend to be really friendly. I dropped by the drive thru and ordering was a breeze. They didn't have a few things I wanted but I was okay with it.
